When is the best time to fly internationally? Thanksgiving.  Few people think of Thanksgiving as a cheap time to travel. For domestic flights, they‚Äôre right. With so many people traveling simultaneously to be back with family, it‚Äôs one of the most expensive weeks all year for intra-U.S. airfare. But all those people traveling domestically are, by definition, not traveling internationally. And while late November is high season in the United States, overseas it‚Äôs very much low season. Thanksgiving is not a holiday in France. Nor is it a holiday in Spain, Italy or other European favorites. Our reporters checked. For many routes, transatlantic flights cost the same as or less than domestic flights. Take a recent search of Thanksgiving-week round-trip flights from New York City to Mobile, Ala., for $469 or Madrid for $498. Or Chicago to Laredo, Texas, for $512 vs. Lisbon for $496. A similar story out of Miami: Peoria, Ill., for $502 or Paris for $465. Caption based on article by Scott Keyes.

Something else is happening to the college application process, for the first time in decades: It‚Äôs becoming easier to get in.  Colleges and universities, on average, are admitting a larger proportion of their applicants than they did 20 years ago, according to new research by the American Enterprise Institute, a conservative think tank. The median acceptance rate at bachelor‚Äôs degree-granting universities and colleges was 7.6 percentage points higher in 2022 than it was in 2012, AEI found. Those are the most recently available admission figures reported to the federal government and do not include institutions with open admission, which accept 100 percent of applicants. This comes after a period of declining acceptance rates and increasing competition to get into college since around the turn of the millennium, which aggravated fears among students and their families that they‚Äôd be rejected by the institutions of their choice.

voice_to_text: Gypsy Rose Blanchard shares details from her baby shower including daughter's name I felt supported exclusive this article came out from people magazine Blanchard tells people she is looking forward to giving my daughter a happiness I never knew growing up then they shared this photo she also confirms the name of their soon to be baby girl Aurora Raina Urker during the baby shower at Lark Secadian Village in Lafayette which we have known the name of the baby for quite some time Ken and I were excited to have a beautiful Celebration that our daughter Aurora Raina Urker that's hard to say can look back on and see how our community welcomed and embraced her with love she will be supported and given all the happiness a child should experience loved ones were present included Blanchard sister Mia and her stepmother Christy while her father was working offshore she tells people I felt supported and happy the baby shower also came complete with fun games which Blanchard refers to as the most memorable part of the festivities during one game guests had to guess the size of the mom to bee's belly by using yarn it was quite funny she said as for her favorite gift Blanchard points to an art piece designed by artist Rebecca Brewer Rivers who is friends with Blanchard's friend Vicky Lewis the piece Blanchard says was made out of the heartbeat of her unborn daughter Gypsy Rose Life after lock up subject also tells people what she's looking forward to the most about motherhood giving my daughter a happiness I never knew growing up she says so the article they go on to explain Gypsy's divorce and some other things from the baby shower and then they wrote as for her future with Erker Blanchard says that while the pair have spoken about plans to get married they're more focused on being parents
